This assay is designed to detect the virus that causes

respiratory infections in Nasopharyngeal specimens, under
a FDA Emergency Use Authorization (May 1st, 2020) and its
performance is limited to qualified high and moderately
complex laboratories designated by CLIA.
Respiratory PCR Panel interpretations:
SARS-CoV-2 Negative (Not Detected) interpretation:
A negative test result for this test means that SARS-CoV-2
RNA was not present in the specimen above the limit of
detection. However, a negative result does not rule out
COVID-19 and should not be used as the sole basis for
treatment, patient management, or epidemiological decisions.
A negative result does not exclude the possibility of
COVID-19.
SARS-CoV-2 Positive (Detected) Interpretation:
The 2019 novel coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2) target nucleic
acids are detected.
SARS-CoV-2 Negative, another respiratory pathogen Positive
(Detected)
If another respiratory pathogen is positive (i.e., Influenza A),
it means that nucleic acid (RNA/DNA) of that pathogen was present
in the specimen above the limit of detection.
Laboratory test results should always be considered in the
context of clinical observations and epidemiological data
in making a final diagnosis and patient management decisions.
